[September 21, 1692]

She was bid to say the Lord''s Prayer. When she came to forgive us our trespasses as we forgive them that trespass against us, she said, so do I. No other mistake in saying the prayer, remarkable.

"A woman''s examination, Sept. 21, 1692" as quoted in Thomas Hutchinson, The History of the Colony and Province of Massachusetts-Bay, 1767. (Cambridge, MA: Harvard University Press, 1936.), vol. II, p. 43n.', 'Court document regarding SWP 100', 'other_documented_accused', NULL, 'From a deposition. By SWP 100, September 21, 1692 (SWP No. 100.3). Dated 1692-09-21. Court document regarding SWP 100', 'SWP No. 100.3', 'salem_project', 1.0, NULL, 1775266565647, 1775266565647, 0);
