[November 8, 1692 ]

James Stevens testifieth and saith that Mary Fitch did say that she felt A woman upon the bed, and put forth hir hand, and felt the hair and felt the hair of hir head and A peg in it, also testifieth that she said she was squesed to pieces, whereas I saw no body hurt hur.

Ipswich Nov''br: the 8th 1692: sworne before us,

*Daniell Epps , J: P:

Tho''s. Wade: J: P:

( Suffolk Court Files Vol. 32, docket No. 2689, p. 17. Massachusetts Supreme Judicial Court, Judicial Archives, Massachusetts State Archives. Boston, MA. )', 'Testimony of James Stevens v. Esther Ellwell ', 'esther_palfrey_2', NULL, 'From a deposition. By SWP 46 — Testimony of James Stevens v. Esther Ellwell  (SWP No. 46.2). Testimony of James Stevens v. Esther Ellwell', 'SWP No. 46.2', 'salem_project', 1.0, NULL, 1775266565648, 1775266565648, 0);
