[July 22, 1692]

We met in a green, which was the minister''s pasture - we were in two companies at last. I think there was a few men with them. - I heard Sarah Good talk of a minister or two. One of them was she that had been at the eastward; his name is Burroughs , and is a little man. -I remember not the other''s name.

William Frederick Poole. The Witchcraft Delusion of 1692. By Gov. Thomas Hutchinson, From an Unpublished Manuscript (An Early Draft of His History of Massachusetts) in the Massachusetts Archives. New England Historical and Genealogical Register, vol. 24: no. 4 (October 1870), p. 401.', 'Fragment of an Examination of Richard Carrier ', 'george_burroughs', NULL, 'From a examination. By SWP 25 — Fragment of an Examination of Richard Carrier , July 22, 1692 (SWP No. 25.5). Dated 1692-07-22. Fragment of an Examination of Richard Carrier', 'SWP No. 25.5', 'salem_project', 1.0, NULL, 1775266565649, 1775266565649, 0);
